    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-25T19:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-25T19:36:00-05:00" n="704"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.00/780</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-25T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1750. Department’s 1656, November 22, 8 p.m. General Eduardo Hay, member of
                    Mexican Claims Commission, stated to-day that commission has been organized and
                    meeting three times weekly for the past three months and hoped in the course of
                    ten days to begin the consideration of individual claims. No reply to the
                    Embassy’s notes on this subject has been received from the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1918-11-29T12:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1918, 12 noon.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1668. Your 1750, November 25, 6 p.m. As commission appears to have been
                        functioning for some time Department must again ask what efforts are being
                        made to obtain replies to Embassy’s notes regarding commission.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
